In plain English
Now that you found DIM_PROVIDER_SPECIALTY_LKP, the way to find specialist visit codes is:
use DIM_PROVIDER_SPECIALTY to link provider to specialty code
use DIM_PROVIDER_SPECIALTY_LKP to translate that code into specialty description/type
identify which providers are specialists
pull claims for those specialist providers
look at the CPT/HCPCS codes on those claims
keep the visit/E&M codes only
That is the correct database-driven method.
Strong starter query
Here is the clean version to start with after replacing your claim procedure table and provider join column:
SELECT
    cp.PROCEDURE_CODE,
    pc.PROCEDURE_NAME,
    pc.PROCEDURE_DESCRIPTION,
    COUNT(*) AS CLAIM_COUNT
FROM YOUR_CLAIM_PROCEDURE_TABLE cp
JOIN FWRB_PRD_WMIDR_DB.CASENET.PROVIDER p
    ON cp.PROVIDER_ID = p.PROVIDER_ID
JOIN FWRB_PRD_WMIDR_DB.BI_ANALYSIS.DIM_PROVIDER_SPECIALTY s
    ON TRY_TO_NUMBER(p.PROVIDER_ID) = s.PROVIDER_ID
JOIN FWRB_PRD_WMIDR_DB.BI_ANALYSIS.DIM_PROVIDER_SPECIALTY_LKP l
    ON s.PROVIDER_SPECIALTY_CODE = l.PROVIDER_SPECIALTY_CODE
LEFT JOIN FWRB_PRD_WMIDR_DB.CASENET.PROCEDURECODE pc
    ON cp.PROCEDURE_CODE = pc.PROCEDURE_CODE
WHERE s.ACTIVE_FLAG = 1
  AND l.ACTIVE_FLAG = 1
  AND l.PROVIDER_SPECIALTY_TYPE = 'SPECIALIST'
  AND (
        cp.PROCEDURE_CODE BETWEEN '99202' AND '99215'
        OR cp.PROCEDURE_CODE = 'G0463'
      )
GROUP BY
    cp.PROCEDURE_CODE,
    pc.PROCEDURE_NAME,
    pc.PROCEDURE_DESCRIPTION
ORDER BY CLAIM_COUNT DESC;
